name: Qwen3.5 (Qwen Code)
description: Open-source AI coding agent framework released by Alibaba's Qwen Team. Includes Qwen Code, a terminal-optimized AI agent with native multimodal capabilities, instruction following, tool usage, and planning capabilities. The release features a 397B-A17B MoE architecture model optimized for logical reasoning, mathematical calculations, and code writing.
community_quotes: Open-source AI agent for the terminal

name: Inspector
description: Visual editing tool for AI coding assistants described as 'Figma for Claude Code'. Connects with Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor to enable click-to-edit functionality - simply click UI elements to make visual adjustments, and Inspector automatically writes changes to the codebase. Eliminates traditional design-to-development handoff processes.
community_quotes: Visual adjustments automatically written to code
